President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed May 18 through May 24, 2019, as National Safe Boating Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he urges all Americans to familiarize themselves with best practices for a safe boating experience. He emphasizes the importance of inspecting boats thoroughly, operating them safely, and ensuring that passengers wear life jackets. The President also encourages participation in boating safety courses and free vessel safety checks offered by the United States Coast Guard. He calls on the Governors of the States and Territories to join him in promoting boating safety through events and activities.